00134   class Exception : public std::runtime_error {
00135     const Exception &operator=(const Exception &); // not assignable
00136 
00137     int m_error;
00138   public:
00139     typedef std::runtime_error Parent;
00140 
00141     Exception(int error) : Parent(""), m_error(error), prev(0) {}
00142     Exception(int error, const String &msg) :
00143               Parent(msg), m_error(error), prev(0) {}
00144     Exception(int error, const String &msg, const Exception &ex) :
00145               Parent(msg), m_error(error), prev(new Exception(ex)) {}
00146     // copy ctor is required for exceptions
00147     Exception(const Exception &ex) : Parent(ex) {
00148       m_error = ex.m_error;
00149       prev = ex.prev ? new Exception(*ex.prev) : 0;
00150     }
00151     ~Exception() throw() { delete prev; }
00152 
00153     int code() const { return m_error; }
00154 
00155     Exception *prev;    // exception chain/list
00156   };
